{{Politics of Libya}}
'''Basic People's Congress''' {{lang-ar|مؤتمر شعبي أساسي}} (Mu'tamar shaʿbi asāsi ) was the smallest administrative subdivision in [[Libya]] under the [[History of Libya under Muammar Gaddafi#Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya (1977–2011)|Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya]] from 1977 to 2012. Geographically it corresponded approximately to the level of a [[township]] or [[borough]].

Under [[Muammar Gaddafi]]'s regime, [[Basic Peoples Congress (political)|political caucuses and committees of the Basic People's Congress]] operated at this level.<ref name="Vandewalle">Vandewalle, Dirk J. (1998) ''Libya since independence: oil and state-building'' I B Tauris,  London, pp. 95-97, {{ISBN|1-86064-264-0}}</ref>  Representatives from the Basic People's Congresses regulated operations at the higher [[Districts of Libya|shabiyah (district)]] level.<ref name="Vandewalle"/>

In July 2013 the [[shabiyat]] and Basic People's Congress system was replaced with a new [[Baladiyat of Libya|baladiyat]] system<ref name="Balaiyat-A">{{Cite web |title=قرار مجلس الوزراء رقم 180 لسنة 2013 ميلادي بإنشاء البلديات |trans-title=Council of Ministers resolution No. 180 for the year 2013 AD the establishment of baladiyat |language=ar |publisher=اللجنة المركزية لانتخاب المجالس البلدية [The Central Committee for the election of baladiyah councils] |url=http://www.ccmce.ly/pdf/2/180_2.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140326232441/http://www.ccmce.ly/pdf/2/180_2.pdf |archivedate=2014-03-26 |deadurl=yes |access-date=2015-12-24 |df= }}</ref> of ninety-nine [[Administrative division|first-level administration subdivisions]].<ref name="Balaiyat-B">{{Cite web |title=الكشف المرفق بقرار مجلس الوزراء رقم 180 لسنة 2013 ميلادي بإنشاء البلديات |trans-title=Appendix Council of Ministers resolution No. 180 for the year 2013 AD the establishment of baladiyat |language=ar |publisher=اللجنة المركزية لانتخاب المجالس البلدية [The Central Committee for the election of baladiyah councils] |url=http://ccmce.ly/web/images/pdf/2/180.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151224011418/http://ccmce.ly/web/images/pdf/2/180.pdf |archivedate=2015-12-24 |deadurl=yes |access-date=2015-12-24 |df= }}</ref>

