[[Image:Map of Donja Dubrava District (Zagreb).svg|thumb|right|Donja Dubrava as a part of [[Zagreb]]]] '''Donja Dubrava''' ({{IPA-sh|dôːɲaː dǔbraʋa|hr}}, "Lower Dubrava") is one of the districts of [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]]. It is located in the northeastern part of the city and in 2011 had 36,363 inhabitants.<ref>{{Croatian Census 2011|url=http://www.dzs.hr/Eng/censuses/census2011/results/htm/e01_01_01_cet/E01_01_01_zup21_cet.html|title=Population by Age and Sex, by Districts of City of Zagreb, 2011 Census}}</ref>
